      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(ci): autoscrub dependency lockfile-only PR changes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds deterministic autoscrubbing for package lockfile-only PR changes when the PR branch is in the main OpenClaw repository or a fork branch with maintainer edits enabled.\n- Restores only changed package lockfiles from the PR base tree using the Git Data API, then creates one narrow cleanup commit: `chore: remove dependency lockfile change`.\n- Leaves unpushable fork PRs and GitHub push failures blocked with a deterministic comment that explains the exact manual next step.\n- Skips autoscrub when any changed `package.json` modifies dependency graph fields, because restoring lockfiles in that case can break frozen installs or dependency semantics.\n\n## User-Facing Comments\n\nThis PR adds one success comment and expands the blocked comment:\n\n- `Dependency lockfile changes were removed`: posted after a successful autoscrub commit, listing restored lockfiles, target branch, and cleanup commit SHA.\n- `Dependency graph changes are blocked`: explains whether autoscrub was not attempted for an unpushable branch, skipped because manifest dependency graph fields changed, or attempted but rejected by GitHub.\n\n## Security / Automation Notes\n\n- The workflow keeps using trusted base checkout under `pull_request_target`; it does not check out or execute PR-head code.\n- `contents: write` is required for the Git Data API cleanup commit path.\n- Autoscrub is limited to PR heads with a concrete ref and SHA where maintainers can modify the branch: same-repository branches or fork branches with maintainer edits enabled.\n- Fork autoscrub writes to the PR head repository/ref and falls back to the blocked comment if GitHub rejects the cleanup commit.\n- Dependency graph changes remain blocked unless the current head SHA is explicitly authorized through the existing secops override flow.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node --check scripts/github/dependency-guard.mjs`\n- YAML parse for `.github/workflows/dependency-guard.yml`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Direct Node assertions for same-repository autoscrub, fork autoscrub denial, maintainer-editable fork autoscrub, and the updated blocked-comment guidance\n\nFocused Vitest note: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/dependency-guard-script.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-guard-workflow.test.ts` hung locally without output in this Codex worktree, matching earlier local runner hangs. CI is the source of truth for those focused tests.\n",
